65void LegacyInlineFlowBox::setHasBadChildList()
66{
67 assertNotDeleted();
68 if (m_hasBadChildList)
69 return;
70 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine())
71 child->setHasBadParent();
72 m_hasBadChildList = true;
73}

77LayoutUnit LegacyInlineFlowBox::getFlowSpacingLogicalWidth()
78{
79 LayoutUnit totalWidth = marginBorderPaddingLogicalLeft() + marginBorderPaddingLogicalRight();
80 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
81 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
82 totalWidth += downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).getFlowSpacingLogicalWidth();
83 }
84 return totalWidth;
85}

87static void setHasTextDescendantsOnAncestors(LegacyInlineFlowBox* box)
88{
89 while (box && !box->hasTextDescendants()) {
90 box->setHasTextDescendants();
91 box = box->parent();
92 }

95void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addToLine(LegacyInlineBox* child)
96{
97 ASSERT(!child->parent());
98 ASSERT(!child->nextOnLine());
99 ASSERT(!child->previousOnLine());
100 checkConsistency();
101
102 child->setParent(this);
103 if (!m_firstChild) {
104 m_firstChild = child;
105 m_lastChild = child;
106 } else {
107 m_lastChild->setNextOnLine(child);
108 child->setPreviousOnLine(m_lastChild);
109 m_lastChild = child;
110 }
111 child->setIsFirstLine(isFirstLine());
112 child->setIsHorizontal(isHorizontal());
113 if (child->behavesLikeText()) {
114 if (child->renderer().parent() == &renderer())
115 m_hasTextChildren = true;
116 setHasTextDescendantsOnAncestors(this);
117 } else if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child)) {
118 if (downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).hasTextDescendants())
119 setHasTextDescendantsOnAncestors(this);
120 }
121 if (descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && !child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
122 const RenderStyle& parentStyle = lineStyle();
123 const RenderStyle& childStyle = child->lineStyle();
124 bool shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = false;
125 if (child->renderer().isReplaced())
126 shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = true;
127 else if (child->behavesLikeText()) {
128 if (child->renderer().isLineBreak() || child->renderer().parent() != &renderer()) {
129 if (!parentStyle.fontCascade().fontMetrics().hasIdenticalAscentDescentAndLineGap(childStyle.fontCascade().fontMetrics())
130 || parentStyle.lineHeight() != childStyle.lineHeight()
131 || (parentStyle.verticalAlign() != VerticalAlign::Baseline && !isRootInlineBox()) || childStyle.verticalAlign() != VerticalAlign::Baseline)
132 shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = true;
133 }
134 if (childStyle.hasTextCombine() || childStyle.textEmphasisMark() != TextEmphasisMark::None)
135 shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = true;
136 } else {
137 if (child->renderer().isLineBreak()) {
138 // FIXME: This isn't ideal. We only turn off because current layout test results expect the <br> to be 0-height on the baseline.
139 // Other than making a zillion tests have to regenerate results, there's no reason to ditch the optimization here.
140 auto childIsHardLinebreak = child->renderer().isBR();
141 shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = childIsHardLinebreak;
142 m_hasHardLinebreak = m_hasHardLinebreak || childIsHardLinebreak;
143 } else {
144 auto& childFlowBox = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child);
145 // Check the child's bit, and then also check for differences in font, line-height, vertical-align
146 if (!childFlowBox.descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline()
147 || !parentStyle.fontCascade().fontMetrics().hasIdenticalAscentDescentAndLineGap(childStyle.fontCascade().fontMetrics())
148 || parentStyle.lineHeight() != childStyle.lineHeight()
149 || (parentStyle.verticalAlign() != VerticalAlign::Baseline && !isRootInlineBox()) || childStyle.verticalAlign() != VerticalAlign::Baseline
150 || childStyle.hasBorder() || childStyle.hasPadding() || childStyle.hasTextCombine())
151 shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline = true;
152 }
153 }
154
155 if (shouldClearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline)
156 clearDescendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline();
157 }
158
159 if (!child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
160 const RenderStyle& childStyle = child->lineStyle();
161 if (child->behavesLikeText()) {
162 const RenderStyle* childStyle = &child->lineStyle();
163 bool hasMarkers = false;
164 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(child)) {
165 const auto* textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(child);
166 hasMarkers = textBox->hasMarkers();
167 }
168 if (childStyle->letterSpacing() < 0 || childStyle->textShadow() || childStyle->textEmphasisMark() != TextEmphasisMark::None || childStyle->hasPositiveStrokeWidth() || hasMarkers || !childStyle->textUnderlineOffset().isAuto() || !childStyle->textDecorationThickness().isAuto() || childStyle->textUnderlinePosition() != TextUnderlinePosition::Auto)
169 child->clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
170 } else if (child->renderer().isReplaced()) {
171 const RenderBox& box = downcast<RenderBox>(child->renderer());
172 if (box.hasRenderOverflow() || box.hasSelfPaintingLayer())
173 child->clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
174 } else if (!child->renderer().isLineBreak() && (childStyle.boxShadow() || child->boxModelObject()->hasSelfPaintingLayer()
175 || (is<RenderListMarker>(child->renderer()) && !downcast<RenderListMarker>(child->renderer()).isInside())
176 || childStyle.hasBorderImageOutsets()))
177 child->clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
178 else if (childStyle.hasOutlineInVisualOverflow())
179 child->clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
180
181 if (lineStyle().hasOutlineInVisualOverflow())
182 clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
183
184 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow() && is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child) && !downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).knownToHaveNoOverflow())
185 clearKnownToHaveNoOverflow();
186 }
187
188 checkConsistency();
189}

191void LegacyInlineFlowBox::removeChild(LegacyInlineBox* child)
192{
193 checkConsistency();
194
195 if (!isDirty())
196 dirtyLineBoxes();
197
198 root().childRemoved(child);
199
200 if (child == m_firstChild)
201 m_firstChild = child->nextOnLine();
202 if (child == m_lastChild)
203 m_lastChild = child->previousOnLine();
204 if (child->nextOnLine())
205 child->nextOnLine()->setPreviousOnLine(child->previousOnLine());
206 if (child->previousOnLine())
207 child->previousOnLine()->setNextOnLine(child->nextOnLine());
208
209 child->setParent(nullptr);
210
211 checkConsistency();
212}
213
214void LegacyInlineFlowBox::deleteLine()
215{
216 LegacyInlineBox* child = firstChild();
217 LegacyInlineBox* next = nullptr;
218 while (child) {
219 ASSERT(this == child->parent());
220 next = child->nextOnLine();
221#ifndef NDEBUG
222 child->setParent(nullptr);
223#endif
224 child->deleteLine();
225 child = next;
226 }
227#ifndef NDEBUG
228 m_firstChild = nullptr;
229 m_lastChild = nullptr;
230#endif
231
232 removeLineBoxFromRenderObject();
233 delete this;
234}

267void LegacyInlineFlowBox::adjustPosition(float dx, float dy)
268{
269 LegacyInlineBox::adjustPosition(dx, dy);
270 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine())
271 child->adjustPosition(dx, dy);
272 if (m_overflow)
273 m_overflow->move(LayoutUnit(dx), LayoutUnit(dy)); // FIXME: Rounding error here since overflow was pixel snapped, but nobody other than list markers passes non-integral values here.
274}

276static inline bool isLastChildForRenderer(const RenderElement& ancestor, const RenderObject* child)
277{
278 if (!child)
279 return false;
280
281 if (child == &ancestor)
282 return true;
283
284 const RenderObject* curr = child;
285 const RenderElement* parent = curr->parent();
286 while (parent && (!parent->isRenderBlock() || parent->isInline())) {
287 if (parent->lastChild() != curr)
288 return false;
289 if (parent == &ancestor)
290 return true;
291
292 curr = parent;
293 parent = curr->parent();
294 }
295
296 return true;
297}
298
299static bool isAncestorAndWithinBlock(const RenderInline& ancestor, const RenderObject* child)
300{
301 const RenderObject* object = child;
302 while (object && (!object->isRenderBlock() || object->isInline())) {
303 if (object == &ancestor)
304 return true;
305 object = object->parent();
306 }
307 return false;
308}

310void LegacyInlineFlowBox::determineSpacingForFlowBoxes(bool lastLine, bool isLogicallyLastRunWrapped, RenderObject* logicallyLastRunRenderer)
311{
312 // All boxes start off open. They will not apply any margins/border/padding on
313 // any side.
314 bool includeLeftEdge = false;
315 bool includeRightEdge = false;
316
317 // The root inline box never has borders/margins/padding.
318 if (parent()) {
319 const auto& inlineFlow = downcast<RenderInline>(renderer());
320
321 bool ltr = renderer().style().isLeftToRightDirection();
322
323 // Check to see if all initial lines are unconstructed. If so, then
324 // we know the inline began on this line (unless we are a continuation).
325 const auto& lineBoxList = inlineFlow.lineBoxes();
326 if (!lineBoxList.firstLineBox()->isConstructed() && !inlineFlow.isContinuation()) {
327#if ENABLE(CSS_BOX_DECORATION_BREAK)
328 if (renderer().style().boxDecorationBreak() == BoxDecorationBreak::Clone)
329 includeLeftEdge = includeRightEdge = true;
330 else
331#endif
332 if (ltr && lineBoxList.firstLineBox() == this)
333 includeLeftEdge = true;
334 else if (!ltr && lineBoxList.lastLineBox() == this)
335 includeRightEdge = true;
336 }
337
338 if (!lineBoxList.lastLineBox()->isConstructed()) {
339 bool isLastObjectOnLine = !isAncestorAndWithinBlock(inlineFlow, logicallyLastRunRenderer) || (isLastChildForRenderer(renderer(), logicallyLastRunRenderer) && !isLogicallyLastRunWrapped);
340
341 // We include the border under these conditions:
342 // (1) The next line was not created, or it is constructed. We check the previous line for rtl.
343 // (2) The logicallyLastRun is not a descendant of this renderer.
344 // (3) The logicallyLastRun is a descendant of this renderer, but it is the last child of this renderer and it does not wrap to the next line.
345#if ENABLE(CSS_BOX_DECORATION_BREAK)
346 // (4) The decoration break is set to clone therefore there will be borders on every sides.
347 if (renderer().style().boxDecorationBreak() == BoxDecorationBreak::Clone)
348 includeLeftEdge = includeRightEdge = true;
349 else
350#endif
351 if (ltr) {
352 if (!nextLineBox()
353 && ((lastLine || isLastObjectOnLine) && !inlineFlow.continuation()))
354 includeRightEdge = true;
355 } else {
356 if ((!prevLineBox() || prevLineBox()->isConstructed())
357 && ((lastLine || isLastObjectOnLine) && !inlineFlow.continuation()))
358 includeLeftEdge = true;
359 }
360 }
361 }
362
363 setEdges(includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge);
364
365 // Recur into our children.
366 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
367 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
368 downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).determineSpacingForFlowBoxes(lastLine, isLogicallyLastRunWrapped, logicallyLastRunRenderer);
369 }
370}

372float LegacyInlineFlowBox::placeBoxesInInlineDirection(float logicalLeft, bool& needsWordSpacing)
373{
374 // Set our x position.
375 beginPlacingBoxRangesInInlineDirection(logicalLeft);
376
377 float startLogicalLeft = logicalLeft;
378 logicalLeft += borderLogicalLeft() + paddingLogicalLeft();
379
380 float minLogicalLeft = startLogicalLeft;
381 float maxLogicalRight = logicalLeft;
382
383 placeBoxRangeInInlineDirection(firstChild(), nullptr, logicalLeft, minLogicalLeft, maxLogicalRight, needsWordSpacing);
384
385 logicalLeft += borderLogicalRight() + paddingLogicalRight();
386 endPlacingBoxRangesInInlineDirection(startLogicalLeft, logicalLeft, minLogicalLeft, maxLogicalRight);
387 return logicalLeft;
388}
389
390float LegacyInlineFlowBox::placeBoxRangeInInlineDirection(LegacyInlineBox* firstChild, LegacyInlineBox* lastChild, float& logicalLeft, float& minLogicalLeft, float& maxLogicalRight, bool& needsWordSpacing)
391{
392 float totalExpansion = 0;
393 for (auto* child = firstChild; child && child != lastChild; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
394 if (is<RenderText>(child->renderer())) {
395 auto& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*child);
396 RenderText& renderText = textBox.renderer();
397 if (renderText.text().length()) {
398 if (needsWordSpacing && isSpaceOrNewline(renderText.characterAt(textBox.start())))
399 logicalLeft += textBox.lineStyle().fontCascade().wordSpacing();
400 needsWordSpacing = !isSpaceOrNewline(renderText.characterAt(textBox.end() - 1));
401 }
402 textBox.setLogicalLeft(logicalLeft);
403 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
404 minLogicalLeft = std::min(logicalLeft, minLogicalLeft);
405 logicalLeft += textBox.logicalWidth();
406 totalExpansion += textBox.expansion();
407 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
408 maxLogicalRight = std::max(logicalLeft, maxLogicalRight);
409 } else {
410 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
411 if (child->renderer().parent()->style().isLeftToRightDirection())
412 child->setLogicalLeft(logicalLeft);
413 else
414 // Our offset that we cache needs to be from the edge of the right border box and
415 // not the left border box. We have to subtract |x| from the width of the block
416 // (which can be obtained from the root line box).
417 child->setLogicalLeft(root().blockFlow().logicalWidth() - logicalLeft);
418 continue; // The positioned object has no effect on the width.
419 }
420 if (is<RenderInline>(child->renderer())) {
421 auto& flow = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child);
422 logicalLeft += flow.marginLogicalLeft();
423 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
424 minLogicalLeft = std::min(logicalLeft, minLogicalLeft);
425 logicalLeft = flow.placeBoxesInInlineDirection(logicalLeft, needsWordSpacing);
426 totalExpansion += flow.expansion();
427 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
428 maxLogicalRight = std::max(logicalLeft, maxLogicalRight);
429 logicalLeft += flow.marginLogicalRight();
430 } else if (!is<RenderListMarker>(child->renderer()) || downcast<RenderListMarker>(child->renderer()).isInside()) {
431 // The box can have a different writing-mode than the overall line, so this is a bit complicated.
432 // Just get all the physical margin and overflow values by hand based off |isVertical|.
433 LayoutUnit logicalLeftMargin = isHorizontal() ? child->boxModelObject()->marginLeft() : child->boxModelObject()->marginTop();
434 LayoutUnit logicalRightMargin = isHorizontal() ? child->boxModelObject()->marginRight() : child->boxModelObject()->marginBottom();
435
436 logicalLeft += logicalLeftMargin;
437 child->setLogicalLeft(logicalLeft);
438 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
439 minLogicalLeft = std::min(logicalLeft, minLogicalLeft);
440 logicalLeft += child->logicalWidth();
441 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
442 maxLogicalRight = std::max(logicalLeft, maxLogicalRight);
443 logicalLeft += logicalRightMargin;
444 // If we encounter any space after this inline block then ensure it is treated as the space between two words.
445 needsWordSpacing = true;
446 }
447 }
448 }
449 setExpansionWithoutGrowing(totalExpansion);
450 return logicalLeft;
451}

453bool LegacyInlineFlowBox::requiresIdeographicBaseline(const GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap) const
454{
455 if (isHorizontal())
456 return false;
457
458 const RenderStyle& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
459 if (lineStyle.fontDescription().orientation() == FontOrientation::Vertical
460 || lineStyle.fontCascade().primaryFont().hasVerticalGlyphs())
461 return true;
462
463 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
464 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
465 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
466
467 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child)) {
468 if (downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).requiresIdeographicBaseline(textBoxDataMap))
469 return true;
470 } else {
471 if (child->lineStyle().fontCascade().primaryFont().hasVerticalGlyphs())
472 return true;
473
474 const Vector<const Font*>* usedFonts = nullptr;
475 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*child)) {
476 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap::const_iterator it = textBoxDataMap.find(downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(child));
477 usedFonts = it == textBoxDataMap.end() ? nullptr : &it->value.first;
478 }
479
480 if (usedFonts) {
481 for (const Font* font : *usedFonts) {
482 if (font->hasVerticalGlyphs())
483 return true;
484 }
485 }
486 }
487 }
488
489 return false;
490}
491
492static bool verticalAlignApplies(const RenderObject& renderer)
493{
494 // http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/visudet.html#propdef-vertical-align - vertical-align only applies to inline level and table-cell elements.
495 // FIXME: Ideally we would only align inline level boxes which means that text inside an inline box would just sit on the box itself.
496 if (!renderer.isText())
497 return true;
498 auto& parentRenderer = *renderer.parent();
499 return (parentRenderer.isInline() && parentRenderer.style().display() != DisplayType::InlineBlock) || parentRenderer.isTableCell();
500}

502void LegacyInlineFlowBox::adjustMaxAscentAndDescent(LayoutUnit& maxAscent, LayoutUnit& maxDescent, LayoutUnit maxPositionTop, LayoutUnit maxPositionBottom)
503{
504 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
505 // The computed lineheight needs to be extended for the
506 // positioned elements
507 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
508 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
509
510 if ((child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Top || child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Bottom) && verticalAlignApplies(child->renderer())) {
511 auto lineHeight = child->lineHeight();
512 if (child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Top) {
513 if (maxAscent + maxDescent < lineHeight)
514 maxDescent = lineHeight - maxAscent;
515 } else {
516 if (maxAscent + maxDescent < lineHeight)
517 maxAscent = lineHeight - maxDescent;
518 }
519
520 if (maxAscent + maxDescent >= std::max(maxPositionTop, maxPositionBottom))
521 break;
522 }
523
524 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
525 downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).adjustMaxAscentAndDescent(maxAscent, maxDescent, maxPositionTop, maxPositionBottom);
526 }
527}
528
529void LegacyInlineFlowBox::computeLogicalBoxHeights(LegacyRootInlineBox& rootBox, LayoutUnit& maxPositionTop, LayoutUnit& maxPositionBottom,
530 LayoutUnit& maxAscent, LayoutUnit& maxDescent, bool& setMaxAscent, bool& setMaxDescent,
531 bool strictMode, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap,
532 FontBaseline baselineType, VerticalPositionCache& verticalPositionCache)
533{
534 // The primary purpose of this function is to compute the maximal ascent and descent values for
535 // a line. These values are computed based off the block's line-box-contain property, which indicates
536 // what parts of descendant boxes have to fit within the line.
537 //
538 // The maxAscent value represents the distance of the highest point of any box (typically including line-height) from
539 // the root box's baseline. The maxDescent value represents the distance of the lowest point of any box
540 // (also typically including line-height) from the root box baseline. These values can be negative.
541 //
542 // A secondary purpose of this function is to store the offset of every box's baseline from the root box's
543 // baseline. This information is cached in the logicalTop() of every box. We're effectively just using
544 // the logicalTop() as scratch space.
545 //
546 // Because a box can be positioned such that it ends up fully above or fully below the
547 // root line box, we only consider it to affect the maxAscent and maxDescent values if some
548 // part of the box (EXCLUDING leading) is above (for ascent) or below (for descent) the root box's baseline.
549 bool affectsAscent = false;
550 bool affectsDescent = false;
551 bool checkChildren = !descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline();
552
553 if (isRootInlineBox()) {
554 // Examine our root box.
555 LayoutUnit ascent;
556 LayoutUnit descent;
557 rootBox.ascentAndDescentForBox(rootBox, textBoxDataMap, ascent, descent, affectsAscent, affectsDescent);
558 if (strictMode || hasTextChildren() || (!checkChildren && hasTextDescendants())) {
559 if (maxAscent < ascent || !setMaxAscent) {
560 maxAscent = ascent;
561 setMaxAscent = true;
562 }
563 if (maxDescent < descent || !setMaxDescent) {
564 maxDescent = descent;
565 setMaxDescent = true;
566 }
567 }
568 }
569
570 if (!checkChildren)
571 return;
572
573 Vector<LegacyInlineBox*> maxAscentInlineBoxList;
574 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
575 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
576 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
577
578 LegacyInlineFlowBox* inlineFlowBox = is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child) ? downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(child) : nullptr;
579
580 bool affectsAscent = false;
581 bool affectsDescent = false;
582
583 // The verticalPositionForBox function returns the distance between the child box's baseline
584 // and the root box's baseline. The value is negative if the child box's baseline is above the
585 // root box's baseline, and it is positive if the child box's baseline is below the root box's baseline.
586 child->setLogicalTop(rootBox.verticalPositionForBox(child, verticalPositionCache));
587
588 LayoutUnit ascent;
589 LayoutUnit descent;
590 rootBox.ascentAndDescentForBox(*child, textBoxDataMap, ascent, descent, affectsAscent, affectsDescent);
591
592 LayoutUnit boxHeight = ascent + descent;
593 if (child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Top && verticalAlignApplies(child->renderer())) {
594 if (maxPositionTop < boxHeight)
595 maxPositionTop = boxHeight;
596 } else if (child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Bottom && verticalAlignApplies(child->renderer())) {
597 if (maxPositionBottom < boxHeight)
598 maxPositionBottom = boxHeight;
599 } else if (strictMode
600 || !inlineFlowBox
601 || inlineFlowBox->hasTextChildren()
602 || (inlineFlowBox->descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && inlineFlowBox->hasTextDescendants())
603 || inlineFlowBox->renderer().hasInlineDirectionBordersOrPadding()
604 || inlineFlowBox->hasHardLinebreak()) {
605 // Note that these values can be negative. Even though we only affect the maxAscent and maxDescent values
606 // if our box (excluding line-height) was above (for ascent) or below (for descent) the root baseline, once you factor in line-height
607 // the final box can end up being fully above or fully below the root box's baseline! This is ok, but what it
608 // means is that ascent and descent (including leading), can end up being negative. The setMaxAscent and
609 // setMaxDescent booleans are used to ensure that we're willing to initially set maxAscent/Descent to negative
610 // values.
611 ascent -= floorf(child->logicalTop());
612 auto isMaxAscent = false;
613 if (affectsAscent) {
614 if (maxAscent < ascent || !setMaxAscent) {
615 maxAscent = ascent;
616 setMaxAscent = true;
617 maxAscentInlineBoxList.clear();
618 }
619 isMaxAscent = maxAscent == ascent;
620 if (isMaxAscent) {
621 // A line can have multiple inline boxes with the same max ascent.
622 maxAscentInlineBoxList.append(child);
623
624 }
625 }
626 // In order to make sure the inline level box is fully enclosed, we should always ceil the descent (containing block's height is max ascent + max descent).
627 // However when the box's logical top is floored (see below), the descent value should also be adjusted in the same direction.
628 descent += isMaxAscent ? floorf(child->logicalTop()) : ceilf(child->logicalTop());
629 if (affectsDescent && (maxDescent < descent || !setMaxDescent)) {
630 maxDescent = descent;
631 setMaxDescent = true;
632 }
633 }
634
635 if (inlineFlowBox) {
636 inlineFlowBox->computeLogicalBoxHeights(rootBox, maxPositionTop, maxPositionBottom, maxAscent, maxDescent,
637 setMaxAscent, setMaxDescent, strictMode, textBoxDataMap, baselineType, verticalPositionCache);
638 }
639 }
640 for (auto* inlineBox : maxAscentInlineBoxList) {
641 // When the inline box stretches the ascent, we floor the logical top value to make sure the inline box does not
642 // stick out of block container at the top (see above).
643 // In such cases the logical top also needs to be adjusted to match this stretched ascent geometry.
644 // (not doing so will result a subpixel logical top offset while it should be flushed with the top edge)
645 inlineBox->setLogicalTop(floorf(inlineBox->logicalTop()));
646 }
647}
648
649void LegacyInlineFlowBox::placeBoxesInBlockDirection(LayoutUnit top, LayoutUnit maxHeight, int maxAscent, bool strictMode, LayoutUnit& lineTop, LayoutUnit& lineBottom, bool& setLineTop,
650 LayoutUnit& lineTopIncludingMargins, LayoutUnit& lineBottomIncludingMargins, bool& hasAnnotationsBefore, bool& hasAnnotationsAfter, FontBaseline baselineType)
651{
652 bool isRootBox = isRootInlineBox();
653 if (isRootBox) {
654 const FontMetrics& fontMetrics = lineStyle().fontMetrics();
655 // RootInlineBoxes are always placed on at pixel boundaries in their logical y direction. Not doing
656 // so results in incorrect rendering of text decorations, most notably underlines.
657 setLogicalTop(roundToInt(top + maxAscent - fontMetrics.ascent(baselineType)));
658 }
659
660 LayoutUnit adjustmentForChildrenWithSameLineHeightAndBaseline;
661 if (descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline()) {
662 adjustmentForChildrenWithSameLineHeightAndBaseline = logicalTop();
663 if (parent())
664 adjustmentForChildrenWithSameLineHeightAndBaseline += renderer().borderAndPaddingBefore();
665 }
666
667 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
668 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
669 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
670
671 if (descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline()) {
672 child->adjustBlockDirectionPosition(adjustmentForChildrenWithSameLineHeightAndBaseline);
673 continue;
674 }
675
676 LegacyInlineFlowBox* inlineFlowBox = is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child) ? downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(child) : nullptr;
677 bool childAffectsTopBottomPos = true;
678
679 if (child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Top && verticalAlignApplies(child->renderer()))
680 child->setLogicalTop(top);
681 else if (child->verticalAlign() == VerticalAlign::Bottom && verticalAlignApplies(child->renderer()))
682 child->setLogicalTop(top + maxHeight - child->lineHeight());
683 else {
684 if (!strictMode && inlineFlowBox && !inlineFlowBox->hasTextChildren() && !inlineFlowBox->renderer().hasInlineDirectionBordersOrPadding()
685 && !(inlineFlowBox->descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && inlineFlowBox->hasTextDescendants()))
686 childAffectsTopBottomPos = false;
687 LayoutUnit posAdjust = maxAscent - child->baselinePosition(baselineType);
688 child->setLogicalTop(child->logicalTop() + top + posAdjust);
689 }
690
691 LayoutUnit newLogicalTop { child->logicalTop() };
692 LayoutUnit newLogicalTopIncludingMargins = newLogicalTop;
693 LayoutUnit boxHeight { child->logicalHeight() };
694 LayoutUnit boxHeightIncludingMargins = boxHeight;
695
696 const RenderStyle& childLineStyle = child->lineStyle();
697 if (child->behavesLikeText() || is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child)) {
698 const FontMetrics& fontMetrics = childLineStyle.fontMetrics();
699 newLogicalTop += child->baselinePosition(baselineType) - fontMetrics.ascent(baselineType);
700 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child)) {
701 RenderBoxModelObject& boxObject = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).renderer();
702 newLogicalTop -= childLineStyle.isHorizontalWritingMode()
703 ? boxObject.borderTop() + boxObject.paddingTop()
704 : boxObject.borderRight() + boxObject.paddingRight();
705 }
706 newLogicalTopIncludingMargins = newLogicalTop;
707 } else if (!child->renderer().isBR()) {
708 const auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(child->renderer());
709 newLogicalTopIncludingMargins = newLogicalTop;
710 // We may flip lines in case of verticalLR mode, so we can assume verticalRL for now.
711 LayoutUnit overSideMargin = child->isHorizontal() ? box.marginTop() : box.marginRight();
712 LayoutUnit underSideMargin = child->isHorizontal() ? box.marginBottom() : box.marginLeft();
713 newLogicalTop += overSideMargin;
714 boxHeightIncludingMargins += overSideMargin + underSideMargin;
715 }
716
717 child->setLogicalTop(newLogicalTop);
718
719 if (childAffectsTopBottomPos) {
720 if (is<RenderRubyRun>(child->renderer())) {
721 // Treat the leading on the first and last lines of ruby runs as not being part of the overall lineTop/lineBottom.
722 // Really this is a workaround hack for the fact that ruby should have been done as line layout and not done using
723 // inline-block.
724 if (renderer().style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode() == (child->renderer().style().rubyPosition() == RubyPosition::After))
725 hasAnnotationsBefore = true;
726 else
727 hasAnnotationsAfter = true;
728
729 auto& rubyRun = downcast<RenderRubyRun>(child->renderer());
730 if (RenderRubyBase* rubyBase = rubyRun.rubyBase()) {
731 LayoutUnit bottomRubyBaseLeading { (child->logicalHeight() - rubyBase->logicalBottom()) + rubyBase->logicalHeight() - (rubyBase->lastRootBox() ? rubyBase->lastRootBox()->lineBottom() : 0_lu) };
732 LayoutUnit topRubyBaseLeading = rubyBase->logicalTop() + (rubyBase->firstRootBox() ? rubyBase->firstRootBox()->lineTop() : 0_lu);
733 newLogicalTop += !renderer().style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? topRubyBaseLeading : bottomRubyBaseLeading;
734 boxHeight -= (topRubyBaseLeading + bottomRubyBaseLeading);
735 }
736 }
737 if (is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*child)) {
738 if (std::optional<bool> markExistsAndIsAbove = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*child).emphasisMarkExistsAndIsAbove(childLineStyle)) {
739 if (*markExistsAndIsAbove != childLineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode())
740 hasAnnotationsBefore = true;
741 else
742 hasAnnotationsAfter = true;
743 }
744 }
745
746 if (!setLineTop) {
747 setLineTop = true;
748 lineTop = newLogicalTop;
749 lineTopIncludingMargins = std::min(lineTop, newLogicalTopIncludingMargins);
750 } else {
751 lineTop = std::min(lineTop, newLogicalTop);
752 lineTopIncludingMargins = std::min(lineTop, std::min(lineTopIncludingMargins, newLogicalTopIncludingMargins));
753 }
754 lineBottom = std::max(lineBottom, newLogicalTop + boxHeight);
755 lineBottomIncludingMargins = std::max(lineBottom, std::max(lineBottomIncludingMargins, newLogicalTopIncludingMargins + boxHeightIncludingMargins));
756 }
757
758 // Adjust boxes to use their real box y/height and not the logical height (as dictated by
759 // line-height).
760 if (inlineFlowBox) {
761 inlineFlowBox->placeBoxesInBlockDirection(top, maxHeight, maxAscent, strictMode, lineTop, lineBottom, setLineTop,
762 lineTopIncludingMargins, lineBottomIncludingMargins, hasAnnotationsBefore, hasAnnotationsAfter, baselineType);
763 }
764 }
765
766 if (isRootBox) {
767 if (strictMode || hasTextChildren() || (descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && hasTextDescendants())) {
768 if (!setLineTop) {
769 setLineTop = true;
770 lineTop = logicalTop();
771 lineTopIncludingMargins = lineTop;
772 } else {
773 lineTop = std::min(lineTop, LayoutUnit(logicalTop()));
774 lineTopIncludingMargins = std::min(lineTop, lineTopIncludingMargins);
775 }
776 lineBottom = std::max(lineBottom, LayoutUnit(logicalBottom()));
777 lineBottomIncludingMargins = std::max(lineBottom, lineBottomIncludingMargins);
778 }
779
780 if (renderer().style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode())
781 flipLinesInBlockDirection(lineTopIncludingMargins, lineBottomIncludingMargins);
782 }
783}
784
785void LegacyInlineFlowBox::maxLogicalBottomForTextDecorationLine(float& maxLogicalBottom, const RenderElement* decorationRenderer, OptionSet<TextDecoration> textDecoration) const
786{
787 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
788 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
789 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
790
791 if (!(child->lineStyle().textDecorationsInEffect() & textDecoration))
792 continue; // If the text decoration isn't in effect on the child, then it must be outside of |decorationRenderer|'s hierarchy.
793
794 if (decorationRenderer && decorationRenderer->isRenderInline() && !isAncestorAndWithinBlock(downcast<RenderInline>(*decorationRenderer), &child->renderer()))
795 continue;
796
797 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
798 downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).maxLogicalBottomForTextDecorationLine(maxLogicalBottom, decorationRenderer, textDecoration);
799 else {
800 if (child->isInlineTextBox() || child->lineStyle().textDecorationSkip().isEmpty())
801 maxLogicalBottom = std::max<float>(maxLogicalBottom, child->logicalBottom());
802 }
803 }
804}
805
806void LegacyInlineFlowBox::minLogicalTopForTextDecorationLine(float& minLogicalTop, const RenderElement* decorationRenderer, OptionSet<TextDecoration> textDecoration) const
807{
808 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
809 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
810 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
811
812 if (!(child->lineStyle().textDecorationsInEffect() & textDecoration))
813 continue; // If the text decoration isn't in effect on the child, then it must be outside of |decorationRenderer|'s hierarchy.
814
815 if (decorationRenderer && decorationRenderer->isRenderInline() && !isAncestorAndWithinBlock(downcast<RenderInline>(*decorationRenderer), &child->renderer()))
816 continue;
817
818 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
819 downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).minLogicalTopForTextDecorationLine(minLogicalTop, decorationRenderer, textDecoration);
820 else {
821 if (child->isInlineTextBox() || child->lineStyle().textDecorationSkip().isEmpty())
822 minLogicalTop = std::min<float>(minLogicalTop, child->logicalTop());
823 }
824 }
825}
826
827void LegacyInlineFlowBox::flipLinesInBlockDirection(LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
828{
829 // Flip the box on the line such that the top is now relative to the lineBottom instead of the lineTop.
830 setLogicalTop(lineBottom - (logicalTop() - lineTop) - logicalHeight());
831
832 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
833 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
834 continue; // Positioned placeholders aren't affected here.
835
836 if (is<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child))
837 downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child).flipLinesInBlockDirection(lineTop, lineBottom);
838 else
839 child->setLogicalTop(lineBottom - (child->logicalTop() - lineTop) - child->logicalHeight());
840 }
841}
842
843inline void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addBoxShadowVisualOverflow(LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow)
844{
845 // box-shadow on root line boxes is applying to the block and not to the lines.
846 if (!parent())
847 return;
848
849 const RenderStyle& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
850 if (!lineStyle.boxShadow())
851 return;
852
853 LayoutUnit boxShadowLogicalTop;
854 LayoutUnit boxShadowLogicalBottom;
855 lineStyle.getBoxShadowBlockDirectionExtent(boxShadowLogicalTop, boxShadowLogicalBottom);
856
857 // Similar to how glyph overflow works, if our lines are flipped, then it's actually the opposite shadow that applies, since
858 // the line is "upside down" in terms of block coordinates.
859 LayoutUnit shadowLogicalTop = lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? -boxShadowLogicalBottom : boxShadowLogicalTop;
860 LayoutUnit shadowLogicalBottom = lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? -boxShadowLogicalTop : boxShadowLogicalBottom;
861
862 LayoutUnit logicalTopVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalTop() + shadowLogicalTop), logicalVisualOverflow.y());
863 LayoutUnit logicalBottomVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalBottom() + shadowLogicalBottom), logicalVisualOverflow.maxY());
864
865 LayoutUnit boxShadowLogicalLeft;
866 LayoutUnit boxShadowLogicalRight;
867 lineStyle.getBoxShadowInlineDirectionExtent(boxShadowLogicalLeft, boxShadowLogicalRight);
868
869 LayoutUnit logicalLeftVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalLeft() + boxShadowLogicalLeft), logicalVisualOverflow.x());
870 LayoutUnit logicalRightVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalRight() + boxShadowLogicalRight), logicalVisualOverflow.maxX());
871
872 logicalVisualOverflow = LayoutRect(logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalTopVisualOverflow, logicalRightVisualOverflow - logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalBottomVisualOverflow - logicalTopVisualOverflow);
873}
874
875inline void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addBorderOutsetVisualOverflow(LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow)
876{
877 // border-image-outset on root line boxes is applying to the block and not to the lines.
878 if (!parent())
879 return;
880
881 const RenderStyle& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
882 if (!lineStyle.hasBorderImageOutsets())
883 return;
884
885 LayoutBoxExtent borderOutsets = lineStyle.borderImageOutsets();
886
887 LayoutUnit borderOutsetLogicalTop = borderOutsets.before(lineStyle.writingMode());
888 LayoutUnit borderOutsetLogicalBottom = borderOutsets.after(lineStyle.writingMode());
889 LayoutUnit borderOutsetLogicalLeft = borderOutsets.start(lineStyle.writingMode());
890 LayoutUnit borderOutsetLogicalRight = borderOutsets.end(lineStyle.writingMode());
891
892 // Similar to how glyph overflow works, if our lines are flipped, then it's actually the opposite border that applies, since
893 // the line is "upside down" in terms of block coordinates. vertical-rl and horizontal-bt are the flipped line modes.
894 LayoutUnit outsetLogicalTop = lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? borderOutsetLogicalBottom : borderOutsetLogicalTop;
895 LayoutUnit outsetLogicalBottom = lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? borderOutsetLogicalTop : borderOutsetLogicalBottom;
896
897 LayoutUnit logicalTopVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalTop() - outsetLogicalTop), logicalVisualOverflow.y());
898 LayoutUnit logicalBottomVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalBottom() + outsetLogicalBottom), logicalVisualOverflow.maxY());
899
900 LayoutUnit outsetLogicalLeft = includeLogicalLeftEdge() ? borderOutsetLogicalLeft : 0_lu;
901 LayoutUnit outsetLogicalRight = includeLogicalRightEdge() ? borderOutsetLogicalRight : 0_lu;
902
903 LayoutUnit logicalLeftVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalLeft() - outsetLogicalLeft), logicalVisualOverflow.x());
904 LayoutUnit logicalRightVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalRight() + outsetLogicalRight), logicalVisualOverflow.maxX());
905
906 logicalVisualOverflow = LayoutRect(logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalTopVisualOverflow, logicalRightVisualOverflow - logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalBottomVisualOverflow - logicalTopVisualOverflow);
907}
908
909inline void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addTextBoxVisualOverflow(LegacyInlineTextBox& textBox, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap, LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow)
910{
911 if (textBox.knownToHaveNoOverflow())
912 return;
913
914 const RenderStyle& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
915
916 GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap::iterator it = textBoxDataMap.find(&textBox);
917 GlyphOverflow* glyphOverflow = it == textBoxDataMap.end() ? nullptr : &it->value.second;
918 bool isFlippedLine = lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode();
919
920 int topGlyphEdge = glyphOverflow ? (isFlippedLine ? glyphOverflow->bottom : glyphOverflow->top) : 0;
921 int bottomGlyphEdge = glyphOverflow ? (isFlippedLine ? glyphOverflow->top : glyphOverflow->bottom) : 0;
922 int leftGlyphEdge = glyphOverflow ? glyphOverflow->left : 0;
923 int rightGlyphEdge = glyphOverflow ? glyphOverflow->right : 0;
924
925 auto viewportSize = textBox.renderer().frame().view() ? textBox.renderer().frame().view()->size() : IntSize();
926 int strokeOverflow = std::ceil(lineStyle.computedStrokeWidth(viewportSize) / 2.0f);
927 int topGlyphOverflow = -strokeOverflow - topGlyphEdge;
928 int bottomGlyphOverflow = strokeOverflow + bottomGlyphEdge;
929 int leftGlyphOverflow = -strokeOverflow - leftGlyphEdge;
930 int rightGlyphOverflow = strokeOverflow + rightGlyphEdge;
931
932 if (std::optional<bool> markExistsAndIsAbove = textBox.emphasisMarkExistsAndIsAbove(lineStyle)) {
933 int emphasisMarkHeight = lineStyle.fontCascade().emphasisMarkHeight(lineStyle.textEmphasisMarkString());
934 if (*markExistsAndIsAbove == !lineStyle.isFlippedLinesWritingMode())
935 topGlyphOverflow = std::min(topGlyphOverflow, -emphasisMarkHeight);
936 else
937 bottomGlyphOverflow = std::max(bottomGlyphOverflow, emphasisMarkHeight);
938 }
939
940 // If letter-spacing is negative, we should factor that into right layout overflow. (Even in RTL, letter-spacing is
941 // applied to the right, so this is not an issue with left overflow.
942 rightGlyphOverflow -= std::min(0, (int)lineStyle.fontCascade().letterSpacing());
943
944 LayoutUnit textShadowLogicalTop;
945 LayoutUnit textShadowLogicalBottom;
946 lineStyle.getTextShadowBlockDirectionExtent(textShadowLogicalTop, textShadowLogicalBottom);
947
948 LayoutUnit childOverflowLogicalTop = std::min<LayoutUnit>(textShadowLogicalTop + topGlyphOverflow, topGlyphOverflow);
949 LayoutUnit childOverflowLogicalBottom = std::max<LayoutUnit>(textShadowLogicalBottom + bottomGlyphOverflow, bottomGlyphOverflow);
950
951 LayoutUnit textShadowLogicalLeft;
952 LayoutUnit textShadowLogicalRight;
953 lineStyle.getTextShadowInlineDirectionExtent(textShadowLogicalLeft, textShadowLogicalRight);
954
955 LayoutUnit childOverflowLogicalLeft = std::min<LayoutUnit>(textShadowLogicalLeft + leftGlyphOverflow, leftGlyphOverflow);
956 LayoutUnit childOverflowLogicalRight = std::max<LayoutUnit>(textShadowLogicalRight + rightGlyphOverflow, rightGlyphOverflow);
957
958 LayoutUnit logicalTopVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(textBox.logicalTop() + childOverflowLogicalTop), logicalVisualOverflow.y());
959 LayoutUnit logicalBottomVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(textBox.logicalBottom() + childOverflowLogicalBottom), logicalVisualOverflow.maxY());
960 LayoutUnit logicalLeftVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(textBox.logicalLeft() + childOverflowLogicalLeft), logicalVisualOverflow.x());
961 LayoutUnit logicalRightVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(textBox.logicalRight() + childOverflowLogicalRight), logicalVisualOverflow.maxX());
962
963 logicalVisualOverflow = LayoutRect(logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalTopVisualOverflow, logicalRightVisualOverflow - logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalBottomVisualOverflow - logicalTopVisualOverflow);
964
965 auto documentMarkerBounds = textBox.calculateUnionOfAllDocumentMarkerBounds();
966 documentMarkerBounds.move(textBox.logicalLeft(), textBox.logicalTop());
967 logicalVisualOverflow = unionRect(logicalVisualOverflow, LayoutRect(documentMarkerBounds));
968
969 textBox.setLogicalOverflowRect(logicalVisualOverflow);
970}
971
972inline void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addOutlineVisualOverflow(LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow)
973{
974 const auto& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
975 if (!lineStyle.hasOutlineInVisualOverflow())
976 return;
977 LayoutUnit outlineSize { lineStyle.outlineSize() };
978 LayoutUnit logicalTopVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalTop() - outlineSize), logicalVisualOverflow.y());
979 LayoutUnit logicalBottomVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalBottom() + outlineSize), logicalVisualOverflow.maxY());
980 LayoutUnit logicalLeftVisualOverflow = std::min(LayoutUnit(logicalLeft() - outlineSize), logicalVisualOverflow.x());
981 LayoutUnit logicalRightVisualOverflow = std::max(LayoutUnit(logicalRight() + outlineSize), logicalVisualOverflow.maxX());
982 logicalVisualOverflow = LayoutRect(logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalTopVisualOverflow,
983 logicalRightVisualOverflow - logicalLeftVisualOverflow, logicalBottomVisualOverflow - logicalTopVisualOverflow);
984}
985
986inline void LegacyInlineFlowBox::addReplacedChildOverflow(const LegacyInlineBox* inlineBox, LayoutRect& logicalLayoutOverflow, LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow)
987{
988 const RenderBox& box = downcast<RenderBox>(inlineBox->renderer());
989
990 // Visual overflow only propagates if the box doesn't have a self-painting layer. This rectangle does not include
991 // transforms or relative positioning (since those objects always have self-painting layers), but it does need to be adjusted
992 // for writing-mode differences.
993 if (!box.hasSelfPaintingLayer()) {
994 LayoutRect childLogicalVisualOverflow = box.logicalVisualOverflowRectForPropagation(&renderer().style());
995 childLogicalVisualOverflow.move(inlineBox->logicalLeft(), inlineBox->logicalTop());
996 logicalVisualOverflow.unite(childLogicalVisualOverflow);
997 }
998
999 // Layout overflow internal to the child box only propagates if the child box doesn't have overflow clip set.
1000 // Otherwise the child border box propagates as layout overflow. This rectangle must include transforms and relative positioning
1001 // and be adjusted for writing-mode differences.
1002 LayoutRect childLogicalLayoutOverflow = box.logicalLayoutOverflowRectForPropagation(&renderer().style());
1003 childLogicalLayoutOverflow.move(inlineBox->logicalLeft(), inlineBox->logicalTop());
1004 logicalLayoutOverflow.unite(childLogicalLayoutOverflow);
1005}
1006
1007void LegacyInlineFlowBox::computeOverflow(LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom, GlyphOverflowAndFallbackFontsMap& textBoxDataMap)
1008{
1009 // If we know we have no overflow, we can just bail.
1010 if (knownToHaveNoOverflow())
1011 return;
1012
1013 if (m_overflow)
1014 m_overflow = nullptr;
1015
1016 // Visual overflow just includes overflow for stuff we need to repaint ourselves. Self-painting layers are ignored.
1017 // Layout overflow is used to determine scrolling extent, so it still includes child layers and also factors in
1018 // transforms, relative positioning, etc.
1019 LayoutRect logicalLayoutOverflow(enclosingLayoutRect(logicalFrameRectIncludingLineHeight(lineTop, lineBottom)));
1020 LayoutRect logicalVisualOverflow(logicalLayoutOverflow);
1021
1022 addBoxShadowVisualOverflow(logicalVisualOverflow);
1023 addOutlineVisualOverflow(logicalVisualOverflow);
1024 addBorderOutsetVisualOverflow(logicalVisualOverflow);
1025
1026 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextOnLine()) {
1027 if (child->renderer().isOutOfFlowPositioned())
1028 continue; // Positioned placeholders don't affect calculations.
1029
1030 if (is<RenderLineBreak>(child->renderer()))
1031 continue;
1032 if (is<RenderText>(child->renderer())) {
1033 auto& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*child);
1034 LayoutRect textBoxOverflow(enclosingLayoutRect(textBox.logicalFrameRect()));
1035 addTextBoxVisualOverflow(textBox, textBoxDataMap, textBoxOverflow);
1036 logicalVisualOverflow.unite(textBoxOverflow);
1037 } else if (is<RenderInline>(child->renderer())) {
1038 auto& flow = downcast<LegacyInlineFlowBox>(*child);
1039 flow.computeOverflow(lineTop, lineBottom, textBoxDataMap);
1040 if (!flow.renderer().hasSelfPaintingLayer())
1041 logicalVisualOverflow.unite(flow.logicalVisualOverflowRect(lineTop, lineBottom));
1042 LayoutRect childLayoutOverflow = flow.logicalLayoutOverflowRect(lineTop, lineBottom);
1043 childLayoutOverflow.move(flow.renderer().relativePositionLogicalOffset());
1044 logicalLayoutOverflow.unite(childLayoutOverflow);
1045 } else
1046 addReplacedChildOverflow(child, logicalLayoutOverflow, logicalVisualOverflow);
1047 }
1048
1049 setOverflowFromLogicalRects(logicalLayoutOverflow, logicalVisualOverflow, lineTop, lineBottom);
1050}
1051
1052void LegacyInlineFlowBox::setLayoutOverflow(const LayoutRect& rect, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
1053{
1054 LayoutRect frameBox = enclosingLayoutRect(frameRectIncludingLineHeight(lineTop, lineBottom));
1055 if (frameBox.contains(rect) || rect.isEmpty())
1056 return;
1057
1058 if (!m_overflow)
1059 m_overflow = adoptRef(new RenderOverflow(frameBox, frameBox));
1060
1061 m_overflow->setLayoutOverflow(rect);
1062}
1063
1064void LegacyInlineFlowBox::setVisualOverflow(const LayoutRect& rect, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
1065{
1066 LayoutRect frameBox = enclosingLayoutRect(frameRectIncludingLineHeight(lineTop, lineBottom));
1067 if (frameBox.contains(rect) || rect.isEmpty())
1068 return;
1069
1070 if (!m_overflow)
1071 m_overflow = adoptRef(new RenderOverflow(frameBox, frameBox));
1072
1073 m_overflow->setVisualOverflow(rect);
1074}
1075
1076void LegacyInlineFlowBox::setOverflowFromLogicalRects(const LayoutRect& logicalLayoutOverflow, const LayoutRect& logicalVisualOverflow, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
1077{
1078 LayoutRect layoutOverflow(isHorizontal() ? logicalLayoutOverflow : logicalLayoutOverflow.transposedRect());
1079 setLayoutOverflow(layoutOverflow, lineTop, lineBottom);
1080
1081 LayoutRect visualOverflow(isHorizontal() ? logicalVisualOverflow : logicalVisualOverflow.transposedRect());
1082 setVisualOverflow(visualOverflow, lineTop, lineBottom);
1083}
1084
1085bool LegacyInlineFlowBox::nodeAtPoint(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom, HitTestAction hitTestAction)
1086{
1087 if (hitTestAction != HitTestForeground)
1088 return false;
1089
1090 LayoutRect overflowRect(visualOverflowRect(lineTop, lineBottom));
1091 flipForWritingMode(overflowRect);
1092 overflowRect.moveBy(accumulatedOffset);
1093 if (!locationInContainer.intersects(overflowRect))
1094 return false;
1095
1096 // Check children first.
1097 // We need to account for culled inline parents of the hit-tested nodes, so that they may also get included in area-based hit-tests.
1098 RenderElement* culledParent = nullptr;
1099 for (auto* child = lastChild(); child; child = child->previousOnLine()) {
1100 if (is<RenderText>(child->renderer()) || !child->boxModelObject()->hasSelfPaintingLayer()) {
1101 RenderElement* newParent = nullptr;
1102 // Culled parents are only relevant for area-based hit-tests, so ignore it in point-based ones.
1103 if (locationInContainer.isRectBasedTest()) {
1104 newParent = child->renderer().parent();
1105 if (newParent == &renderer())
1106 newParent = nullptr;
1107 }
1108 // Check the culled parent after all its children have been checked, to do this we wait until
1109 // we are about to test an element with a different parent.
1110 if (newParent != culledParent) {
1111 if (!newParent || !newParent->isDescendantOf(culledParent)) {
1112 while (culledParent && culledParent != &renderer() && culledParent != newParent) {
1113 if (is<RenderInline>(*culledParent) && downcast<RenderInline>(*culledParent).hitTestCulledInline(request, result, locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
1114 return true;
1115 culledParent = culledParent->parent();
1116 }
1117 }
1118 culledParent = newParent;
1119 }
1120 if (child->nodeAtPoint(request, result, locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset, lineTop, lineBottom, hitTestAction)) {
1121 renderer().updateHitTestResult(result, locationInContainer.point() - toLayoutSize(accumulatedOffset));
1122 return true;
1123 }
1124 }
1125 }
1126 // Check any culled ancestor of the final children tested.
1127 while (culledParent && culledParent != &renderer()) {
1128 if (is<RenderInline>(*culledParent) && downcast<RenderInline>(*culledParent).hitTestCulledInline(request, result, locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
1129 return true;
1130 culledParent = culledParent->parent();
1131 }
1132
1133 // Now check ourselves. Pixel snap hit testing.
1134 if (!visibleToHitTesting(request))
1135 return false;
1136
1137 // Do not hittest content beyond the ellipsis box.
1138 if (isRootInlineBox() && hasEllipsisBox()) {
1139 const LegacyEllipsisBox* ellipsisBox = root().ellipsisBox();
1140 FloatRect boundsRect(frameRect());
1141
1142 if (isHorizontal())
1143 renderer().style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? boundsRect.shiftXEdgeTo(ellipsisBox->right()) : boundsRect.setWidth(ellipsisBox->left() - left());
1144 else
1145 boundsRect.shiftYEdgeTo(ellipsisBox->right());
1146
1147 flipForWritingMode(boundsRect);
1148 boundsRect.moveBy(accumulatedOffset);
1149 // We are beyond the ellipsis box.
1150 if (locationInContainer.intersects(boundsRect))
1151 return false;
1152 }
1153
1154 // Constrain our hit testing to the line top and bottom if necessary.
1155 bool noQuirksMode = renderer().document().inNoQuirksMode();
1156 if (!noQuirksMode && !hasTextChildren() && !(descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && hasTextDescendants())) {
1157 LegacyRootInlineBox& rootBox = root();
1158 LayoutUnit top { isHorizontal() ? y() : x()};
1159 LayoutUnit logicalHeight { isHorizontal() ? height() : width() };
1160 LayoutUnit bottom = std::min(rootBox.lineBottom(), top + logicalHeight);
1161 top = std::max(rootBox.lineTop(), top);
1162 logicalHeight = bottom - top;
1163 }
1164
1165 // Move x/y to our coordinates.
1166 FloatRect rect(frameRect());
1167 flipForWritingMode(rect);
1168 rect.moveBy(accumulatedOffset);
1169
1170 if (locationInContainer.intersects(rect)) {
1171 renderer().updateHitTestResult(result, flipForWritingMode(locationInContainer.point() - toLayoutSize(accumulatedOffset))); // Don't add in m_x or m_y here, we want coords in the containing block's space.
1172 if (result.addNodeToListBasedTestResult(renderer().nodeForHitTest(), request, locationInContainer, rect) == HitTestProgress::Stop)
1173 return true;
1174 }
1175
1176 return false;
1177}
1178
1179void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paint(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
1180{
1181 if (paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Foreground && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Selection && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Outline && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::SelfOutline && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::ChildOutlines && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::TextClip && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Mask && paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::EventRegion)
1182 return;
1183
1184 LayoutRect overflowRect(visualOverflowRect(lineTop, lineBottom));
1185 flipForWritingMode(overflowRect);
1186 overflowRect.moveBy(paintOffset);
1187
1188 if (!paintInfo.rect.intersects(snappedIntRect(overflowRect)))
1189 return;
1190
1191 if (paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::ChildOutlines) {
1192 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Outline || paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::SelfOutline) {
1193 // Add ourselves to the paint info struct's list of inlines that need to paint their
1194 // outlines.
1195 if (renderer().style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && renderer().hasOutline() && !isRootInlineBox()) {
1196 RenderInline& inlineFlow = downcast<RenderInline>(renderer());
1197
1198 RenderBlock* containingBlock = nullptr;
1199 bool containingBlockPaintsContinuationOutline = inlineFlow.continuation() || inlineFlow.isContinuation();
1200 if (containingBlockPaintsContinuationOutline) {
1201 // FIXME: See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=54690. We currently don't reconnect inline continuations
1202 // after a child removal. As a result, those merged inlines do not get seperated and hence not get enclosed by
1203 // anonymous blocks. In this case, it is better to bail out and paint it ourself.
1204 RenderBlock* enclosingAnonymousBlock = renderer().containingBlock();
1205 if (!enclosingAnonymousBlock->isAnonymousBlock())
1206 containingBlockPaintsContinuationOutline = false;
1207 else {
1208 containingBlock = enclosingAnonymousBlock->containingBlock();
1209 for (auto* box = &renderer(); box != containingBlock; box = &box->parent()->enclosingBoxModelObject()) {
1210 if (box->hasSelfPaintingLayer()) {
1211 containingBlockPaintsContinuationOutline = false;
1212 break;
1213 }
1214 }
1215 }
1216 }
1217
1218 if (containingBlockPaintsContinuationOutline) {
1219 // Add ourselves to the containing block of the entire continuation so that it can
1220 // paint us atomically.
1221 containingBlock->addContinuationWithOutline(downcast<RenderInline>(renderer().element()->renderer()));
1222 } else if (!inlineFlow.isContinuation())
1223 paintInfo.outlineObjects->add(&inlineFlow);
1224 }
1225 } else if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Mask)
1226 paintMask(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1227 else {
1228 // Paint our background, border and box-shadow.
1229 paintBoxDecorations(paintInfo, paintOffset);
1230 }
1231 }
1232
1233 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Mask)
1234 return;
1235
1236 PaintPhase paintPhase = paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::ChildOutlines ? PaintPhase::Outline : paintInfo.phase;
1237 PaintInfo childInfo(paintInfo);
1238 childInfo.phase = paintPhase;
1239 childInfo.updateSubtreePaintRootForChildren(&renderer());
1240
1241 // Paint our children.
1242 if (paintPhase != PaintPhase::SelfOutline) {
1243 for (auto* curr = firstChild(); curr; curr = curr->nextOnLine()) {
1244 if (curr->renderer().isText() || !curr->boxModelObject()->hasSelfPaintingLayer())
1245 curr->paint(childInfo, paintOffset, lineTop, lineBottom);
1246 }
1247 }
1248}
1249
1250void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paintFillLayers(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const Color& color, const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutRect& rect, CompositeOperator op)
1251{
1252 Vector<const FillLayer*, 8> layers;
1253 for (auto* layer = &fillLayer; layer; layer = layer->next())
1254 layers.append(layer);
1255 layers.reverse();
1256 for (auto* layer : layers)
1257 paintFillLayer(paintInfo, color, *layer, rect, op);
1258}
1259
1260bool LegacyInlineFlowBox::boxShadowCanBeAppliedToBackground(const FillLayer& lastBackgroundLayer) const
1261{
1262 // The checks here match how paintFillLayer() decides whether to clip (if it does, the shadow
1263 // would be clipped out, so it has to be drawn separately).
1264 StyleImage* image = lastBackgroundLayer.image();
1265 bool hasFillImage = image && image->canRender(&renderer(), renderer().style().effectiveZoom());
1266 return (!hasFillImage && !renderer().style().hasBorderRadius()) || (!prevLineBox() && !nextLineBox()) || !parent();
1267}
1268
1269void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paintFillLayer(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const Color& color, const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutRect& rect, CompositeOperator op)
1270{
1271 auto* image = fillLayer.image();
1272 bool hasFillImage = image && image->canRender(&renderer(), renderer().style().effectiveZoom());
1273 if ((!hasFillImage && !renderer().style().hasBorderRadius()) || (!prevLineBox() && !nextLineBox()) || !parent())
1274 renderer().paintFillLayerExtended(paintInfo, color, fillLayer, rect, BackgroundBleedNone, this, rect.size(), op);
1275#if ENABLE(CSS_BOX_DECORATION_BREAK)
1276 else if (renderer().style().boxDecorationBreak() == BoxDecorationBreak::Clone) {
1277 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(paintInfo.context());
1278 paintInfo.context().clip({ rect.x(), rect.y(), LayoutUnit(width()), LayoutUnit(height()) });
1279 renderer().paintFillLayerExtended(paintInfo, color, fillLayer, rect, BackgroundBleedNone, this, rect.size(), op);
1280 }
1281#endif
1282 else {
1283 // We have a fill image that spans multiple lines.
1284 // We need to adjust tx and ty by the width of all previous lines.
1285 // Think of background painting on inlines as though you had one long line, a single continuous
1286 // strip. Even though that strip has been broken up across multiple lines, you still paint it
1287 // as though you had one single line. This means each line has to pick up the background where
1288 // the previous line left off.
1289 LayoutUnit logicalOffsetOnLine;
1290 LayoutUnit totalLogicalWidth;
1291 if (renderer().style().direction() == TextDirection::LTR) {
1292 for (auto* curr = prevLineBox(); curr; curr = curr->prevLineBox())
1293 logicalOffsetOnLine += curr->logicalWidth();
1294 totalLogicalWidth = logicalOffsetOnLine;
1295 for (auto* curr = this; curr; curr = curr->nextLineBox())
1296 totalLogicalWidth += curr->logicalWidth();
1297 } else {
1298 for (auto* curr = nextLineBox(); curr; curr = curr->nextLineBox())
1299 logicalOffsetOnLine += curr->logicalWidth();
1300 totalLogicalWidth = logicalOffsetOnLine;
1301 for (auto* curr = this; curr; curr = curr->prevLineBox())
1302 totalLogicalWidth += curr->logicalWidth();
1303 }
1304 LayoutUnit stripX = rect.x() - (isHorizontal() ? logicalOffsetOnLine : 0_lu);
1305 LayoutUnit stripY = rect.y() - (isHorizontal() ? 0_lu : logicalOffsetOnLine);
1306 LayoutUnit stripWidth = isHorizontal() ? totalLogicalWidth : LayoutUnit(width());
1307 LayoutUnit stripHeight = isHorizontal() ? LayoutUnit(height()) : totalLogicalWidth;
1308
1309 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(paintInfo.context());
1310 paintInfo.context().clip({ rect.x(), rect.y(), LayoutUnit(width()), LayoutUnit(height()) });
1311 renderer().paintFillLayerExtended(paintInfo, color, fillLayer, LayoutRect(stripX, stripY, stripWidth, stripHeight), BackgroundBleedNone, this, rect.size(), op);
1312 }
1313}
1314
1315void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paintBoxShadow(const PaintInfo& info, const RenderStyle& style, ShadowStyle shadowStyle, const LayoutRect& paintRect)
1316{
1317 if ((!prevLineBox() && !nextLineBox()) || !parent())
1318 renderer().paintBoxShadow(info, paintRect, style, shadowStyle);
1319 else {
1320 // FIXME: We can do better here in the multi-line case. We want to push a clip so that the shadow doesn't
1321 // protrude incorrectly at the edges, and we want to possibly include shadows cast from the previous/following lines
1322 renderer().paintBoxShadow(info, paintRect, style, shadowStyle, includeLogicalLeftEdge(), includeLogicalRightEdge());
1323 }
1324}
1325
1326void LegacyInlineFlowBox::constrainToLineTopAndBottomIfNeeded(LayoutRect& rect) const
1327{
1328 bool noQuirksMode = renderer().document().inNoQuirksMode();
1329 if (!noQuirksMode && !hasTextChildren() && !(descendantsHaveSameLineHeightAndBaseline() && hasTextDescendants())) {
1330 const LegacyRootInlineBox& rootBox = root();
1331 LayoutUnit logicalTop = isHorizontal() ? rect.y() : rect.x();
1332 LayoutUnit logicalHeight = isHorizontal() ? rect.height() : rect.width();
1333 LayoutUnit bottom = std::min(rootBox.lineBottom(), logicalTop + logicalHeight);
1334 logicalTop = std::max(rootBox.lineTop(), logicalTop);
1335 logicalHeight = bottom - logicalTop;
1336 if (isHorizontal()) {
1337 rect.setY(logicalTop);
1338 rect.setHeight(logicalHeight);
1339 } else {
1340 rect.setX(logicalTop);
1341 rect.setWidth(logicalHeight);
1342 }
1343 }
1344}
1345
1346static LayoutRect clipRectForNinePieceImageStrip(LegacyInlineFlowBox* box, const NinePieceImage& image, const LayoutRect& paintRect)
1347{
1348 LayoutRect clipRect(paintRect);
1349 auto& style = box->renderer().style();
1350 LayoutBoxExtent outsets = style.imageOutsets(image);
1351 if (box->isHorizontal()) {
1352 clipRect.setY(paintRect.y() - outsets.top());
1353 clipRect.setHeight(paintRect.height() + outsets.top() + outsets.bottom());
1354 if (box->includeLogicalLeftEdge()) {
1355 clipRect.setX(paintRect.x() - outsets.left());
1356 clipRect.setWidth(paintRect.width() + outsets.left());
1357 }
1358 if (box->includeLogicalRightEdge())
1359 clipRect.setWidth(clipRect.width() + outsets.right());
1360 } else {
1361 clipRect.setX(paintRect.x() - outsets.left());
1362 clipRect.setWidth(paintRect.width() + outsets.left() + outsets.right());
1363 if (box->includeLogicalLeftEdge()) {
1364 clipRect.setY(paintRect.y() - outsets.top());
1365 clipRect.setHeight(paintRect.height() + outsets.top());
1366 }
1367 if (box->includeLogicalRightEdge())
1368 clipRect.setHeight(clipRect.height() + outsets.bottom());
1369 }
1370 return clipRect;
1371}
1372
1373void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paintBoxDecorations(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1374{
1375 if (!paintInfo.shouldPaintWithinRoot(renderer()) || renderer().style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible || paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Foreground)
1376 return;
1377
1378 // You can use p::first-line to specify a background. If so, the root line boxes for
1379 // a line may actually have to paint a background.
1380 if (parent() && !renderer().hasVisibleBoxDecorations())
1381 return;
1382 const RenderStyle& lineStyle = this->lineStyle();
1383 if (!parent() && (!isFirstLine() || &lineStyle == &renderer().style()))
1384 return;
1385
1386 LayoutRect frameRect(this->frameRect());
1387 constrainToLineTopAndBottomIfNeeded(frameRect);
1388
1389 // Move x/y to our coordinates.
1390 LayoutRect localRect(frameRect);
1391 flipForWritingMode(localRect);
1392
1393 LayoutPoint adjustedPaintoffset = paintOffset + localRect.location();
1394 GraphicsContext& context = paintInfo.context();
1395 LayoutRect paintRect = LayoutRect(adjustedPaintoffset, frameRect.size());
1396 // Shadow comes first and is behind the background and border.
1397 if (!renderer().boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(adjustedPaintoffset, BackgroundBleedNone, this))
1398 paintBoxShadow(paintInfo, lineStyle, ShadowStyle::Normal, paintRect);
1399
1400 auto color = lineStyle.visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1401 auto compositeOp = renderer().document().compositeOperatorForBackgroundColor(color, renderer());
1402
1403 color = lineStyle.colorByApplyingColorFilter(color);
1404
1405 paintFillLayers(paintInfo, color, lineStyle.backgroundLayers(), paintRect, compositeOp);
1406 paintBoxShadow(paintInfo, lineStyle, ShadowStyle::Inset, paintRect);
1407
1408 // :first-line cannot be used to put borders on a line. Always paint borders with our
1409 // non-first-line style.
1410 if (!parent() || !renderer().style().hasVisibleBorderDecoration())
1411 return;
1412 const NinePieceImage& borderImage = renderer().style().borderImage();
1413 StyleImage* borderImageSource = borderImage.image();
1414 bool hasBorderImage = borderImageSource && borderImageSource->canRender(&renderer(), lineStyle.effectiveZoom());
1415 if (hasBorderImage && !borderImageSource->isLoaded())
1416 return; // Don't paint anything while we wait for the image to load.
1417
1418 // The simple case is where we either have no border image or we are the only box for this object. In those
1419 // cases only a single call to draw is required.
1420 if (!hasBorderImage || (!prevLineBox() && !nextLineBox()))
1421 renderer().paintBorder(paintInfo, paintRect, lineStyle, BackgroundBleedNone, includeLogicalLeftEdge(), includeLogicalRightEdge());
1422 else {
1423 // We have a border image that spans multiple lines.
1424 // We need to adjust tx and ty by the width of all previous lines.
1425 // Think of border image painting on inlines as though you had one long line, a single continuous
1426 // strip. Even though that strip has been broken up across multiple lines, you still paint it
1427 // as though you had one single line. This means each line has to pick up the image where
1428 // the previous line left off.
1429 // FIXME: What the heck do we do with RTL here? The math we're using is obviously not right,
1430 // but it isn't even clear how this should work at all.
1431 LayoutUnit logicalOffsetOnLine;
1432 for (auto* curr = prevLineBox(); curr; curr = curr->prevLineBox())
1433 logicalOffsetOnLine += curr->logicalWidth();
1434 LayoutUnit totalLogicalWidth = logicalOffsetOnLine;
1435 for (auto* curr = this; curr; curr = curr->nextLineBox())
1436 totalLogicalWidth += curr->logicalWidth();
1437 LayoutUnit stripX = adjustedPaintoffset.x() - (isHorizontal() ? logicalOffsetOnLine : 0_lu);
1438 LayoutUnit stripY = adjustedPaintoffset.y() - (isHorizontal() ? 0_lu : logicalOffsetOnLine);
1439 LayoutUnit stripWidth = isHorizontal() ? totalLogicalWidth : frameRect.width();
1440 LayoutUnit stripHeight = isHorizontal() ? frameRect.height() : totalLogicalWidth;
1441
1442 LayoutRect clipRect = clipRectForNinePieceImageStrip(this, borderImage, paintRect);
1443 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
1444 context.clip(clipRect);
1445 renderer().paintBorder(paintInfo, LayoutRect(stripX, stripY, stripWidth, stripHeight), lineStyle);
1446 }
1447}
1448
1449void LegacyInlineFlowBox::paintMask(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1450{
1451 if (!paintInfo.shouldPaintWithinRoot(renderer()) || renderer().style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible || paintInfo.phase != PaintPhase::Mask)
1452 return;
1453
1454 LayoutRect frameRect(this->frameRect());
1455 constrainToLineTopAndBottomIfNeeded(frameRect);
1456
1457 // Move x/y to our coordinates.
1458 LayoutRect localRect(frameRect);
1459 flipForWritingMode(localRect);
1460 LayoutPoint adjustedPaintOffset = paintOffset + localRect.location();
1461
1462 const NinePieceImage& maskNinePieceImage = renderer().style().maskBoxImage();
1463 StyleImage* maskBoxImage = renderer().style().maskBoxImage().image();
1464
1465 // Figure out if we need to push a transparency layer to render our mask.
1466 bool pushTransparencyLayer = false;
1467 bool compositedMask = renderer().hasLayer() && renderer().layer()->hasCompositedMask();
1468 bool flattenCompositingLayers = renderer().view().frameView().paintBehavior().contains(PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers);
1469 CompositeOperator compositeOp = CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
1470 if (!compositedMask || flattenCompositingLayers) {
1471 if ((maskBoxImage && renderer().style().maskLayers().hasImage()) || renderer().style().maskLayers().next())
1472 pushTransparencyLayer = true;
1473
1474 compositeOp = CompositeOperator::DestinationIn;
1475 if (pushTransparencyLayer) {
1476 paintInfo.context().setCompositeOperation(CompositeOperator::DestinationIn);
1477 paintInfo.context().beginTransparencyLayer(1.0f);
1478 compositeOp = CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
1479 }
1480 }
1481
1482 LayoutRect paintRect = LayoutRect(adjustedPaintOffset, frameRect.size());
1483 paintFillLayers(paintInfo, Color(), renderer().style().maskLayers(), paintRect, compositeOp);
1484
1485 bool hasBoxImage = maskBoxImage && maskBoxImage->canRender(&renderer(), renderer().style().effectiveZoom());
1486 if (!hasBoxImage || !maskBoxImage->isLoaded()) {
1487 if (pushTransparencyLayer)
1488 paintInfo.context().endTransparencyLayer();
1489 return; // Don't paint anything while we wait for the image to load.
1490 }
1491
1492 // The simple case is where we are the only box for this object. In those
1493 // cases only a single call to draw is required.
1494 if (!prevLineBox() && !nextLineBox())
1495 renderer().paintNinePieceImage(paintInfo.context(), LayoutRect(adjustedPaintOffset, frameRect.size()), renderer().style(), maskNinePieceImage, compositeOp);
1496 else {
1497 // We have a mask image that spans multiple lines.
1498 // We need to adjust _tx and _ty by the width of all previous lines.
1499 LayoutUnit logicalOffsetOnLine;
1500 for (auto* curr = prevLineBox(); curr; curr = curr->prevLineBox())
1501 logicalOffsetOnLine += curr->logicalWidth();
1502 LayoutUnit totalLogicalWidth = logicalOffsetOnLine;
1503 for (auto* curr = this; curr; curr = curr->nextLineBox())
1504 totalLogicalWidth += curr->logicalWidth();
1505 LayoutUnit stripX = adjustedPaintOffset.x() - (isHorizontal() ? logicalOffsetOnLine : 0_lu);
1506 LayoutUnit stripY = adjustedPaintOffset.y() - (isHorizontal() ? 0_lu : logicalOffsetOnLine);
1507 LayoutUnit stripWidth = isHorizontal() ? totalLogicalWidth : frameRect.width();
1508 LayoutUnit stripHeight = isHorizontal() ? frameRect.height() : totalLogicalWidth;
1509
1510 LayoutRect clipRect = clipRectForNinePieceImageStrip(this, maskNinePieceImage, paintRect);
1511 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(paintInfo.context());
1512 paintInfo.context().clip(clipRect);
1513 renderer().paintNinePieceImage(paintInfo.context(), LayoutRect(stripX, stripY, stripWidth, stripHeight), renderer().style(), maskNinePieceImage, compositeOp);
1514 }
1515
1516 if (pushTransparencyLayer)
1517 paintInfo.context().endTransparencyLayer();
1518}

1541bool LegacyInlineFlowBox::canAccommodateEllipsis(bool ltr, int blockEdge, int ellipsisWidth) const
1542{
1543 for (auto* box = firstChild(); box; box = box->nextOnLine()) {

1545 return false;
1546 }
1547 return true;

1549
1550float LegacyInlineFlowBox::placeEllipsisBox(bool ltr, float blockLeftEdge, float blockRightEdge, float ellipsisWidth, float &truncatedWidth, bool& foundBox)
1551{
1552 float result = -1;
1553 // We iterate over all children, the foundBox variable tells us when we've found the
1554 // box containing the ellipsis. All boxes after that one in the flow are hidden.
1555 // If our flow is ltr then iterate over the boxes from left to right, otherwise iterate
1556 // from right to left. Varying the order allows us to correctly hide the boxes following the ellipsis.
1557 LegacyInlineBox* box = ltr ? firstChild() : lastChild();
1558
1559 // NOTE: these will cross after foundBox = true.
1560 int visibleLeftEdge = blockLeftEdge;
1561 int visibleRightEdge = blockRightEdge;
1562
1563 while (box) {
1564 int currResult = box->placeEllipsisBox(ltr, visibleLeftEdge, visibleRightEdge, ellipsisWidth, truncatedWidth, foundBox);
1565 if (currResult != -1 && result == -1)
1566 result = currResult;
1567
1568 if (ltr) {
1569 visibleLeftEdge += box->logicalWidth();
1570 box = box->nextOnLine();
1571 } else {
1572 visibleRightEdge -= box->logicalWidth();
1573 box = box->previousOnLine();
1574 }
1575 }
1576 return result;
1577}
